f=Brand Studio/atlas/marketplace/brand-identity/SKILL.md · tx=<!-- Unmodified copy "brand-identity" (rampstackco repo vista's okr-design candidate; consistently high-quality practitioner content). Added small-business path: new toongine business visual identity runs skill create system elements: logo system, color, typography, imagery/iconography, motion), output populates brand-kit file atlas's brand-guidelines skill enforces ever after. BOUNDARY NOTES system: source references sibling skills (brand-ideation, brand-style-guide, brand-voice, design-standards) copied here. brand-voice territory belongs LENA department atlas produces visual system only, voice sections defer her. Output feeds custom/brand-guidelines/assets/brand-kit-template.md creation here, enforcement there. accessibility reference (WCAG math, contrast checker snippet) part copy atlas applies creating palettes, brand-guidelines re-checks audit time. --> · h1:Brand Identity=Design evaluate visual artifacts express brand: logo system, color, typography, imagery, iconography, motion. Stack-agnostic. Tool-agnostic. skill assumes brand direction already approved (positioning, mood, name). not, run `brand-ideation` first. · h2:Required inputs=brand name approved positioning, mood direction (from ideation, supplied references), Audience and category context, Application contexts (web, print, packaging, motion whatever applies), Constraints (parent brand requirements, regulatory marks, accessibility minimums) · wf=**Confirm brand direction.** Positioning, mood, audience. unclear, return `brand-ideation`. **Audit applications.** List place brand appear (web, print, packaging, app, social, signage, video). application contexts drive what system needs handle. **Element-by-element design.** Start logo color, since constrain typography. type. imagery, iconography, motion. **Stress-test.** Apply system mock applications (homepage, social post, business card, product UI, signage). break? Iterate. **Document.** element rules, examples, dos/don'ts. becomes input `brand-style-guide`. **Get sign-off** before broad rollout. Identity changes after rollout 10x cost changes during design. · h2:Output format=Default output structured set files: · h2:Output format=`identity/logo/` logo variants (SVG primary, plus PNG/JPG exports common sizes), `identity/colors.md` Color system hex codes, contrast ratios, usage rules, `identity/typography.md` Type system scale, weights, fallbacks, `identity/imagery.md` Imagery direction reference examples, `identity/iconography/` Icon set icon style spec, `identity/motion.md` - Motion principles, `identity/applications/` application mockups stress-testing system · h2:Output format=feed directly `brand-style-guide`.